other_tests.findings: The appendix is enlarged with hyperemic walls and surrounding fat stranding consistent with acute appendicitis. No bowel obstruction, diverticulitis, or significant lymphadenopathy is observed. A 3-cm cystic structure in the right adnexa is unchanged in appearance and size compared to CT abdomen and pelvis on a previous date.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The cystic structure in the right adnexa is unchanged in appearance and size compared to prior imaging.
